---
source: crates/kul-wasm/tests/format.rs
expression: formatted
---
# A multi-file project — file 1 of 3: the founders.
#
# A Kul project is a directory: one `kul.yml` manifest plus any number of
# `.kul` files beside it. All files share ONE flat namespace — every
# `person` and `marriage` id is visible from every file, with no imports
# and no prefixes. So you are free to split a family however suits the
# archive; here it is split by generation across three files.
#
# Ids declared here (the founders and their marriage) are referenced by
# `birth` lines in the other files. Declaration order across files does
# not matter — references resolve in both directions.

person diego   name:"Diego Fernández"   gender:male    born:~1935
person carmen  name:"Carmen Fernández"  gender:female  born:1938-07-19

marriage m_diego_carmen diego carmen  start:1960-02-14
